I installed this extension to detect the browser (user agent) viewing a page to adapt page content.&#13;
&#13;
Unfortunately, the code below placed in a template seems to extract all browsers installed on my PC !&#13;
&lt;code&gt;&#13;
{def $server_vars=ezservervars()} &#13;
Browser ={$server_vars['HTTP_USER_AGENT']}&#13;
&lt;/code&gt;&#13;
&#13;
I have this same result, no matter the browser : &#13;
"Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.0) AppleWebKit/535.1 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/14.0.835.186 Safari/535.1&#13;
&#13;
=&gt; How could I get the browser that is currently displaying the page ?&#13;
